Write a python standalone application “ecflow workflow generator” to generate the ecflow workflow. 
The ecflow workflow generator will prompt for user input on all following:
Workflow environment variable:
suite - a name that identify the ecflow suite. Such as “nco_aqm”
model - the model name that will be assigned as “model” in python variable. Such as “aqm”.
model_ver - a three digit number lead by character “v”. Such as “v7.0.8”
packageroot - a name pair variable separated by common that contains:
Machine_Platform - Select one supercomputer platform wcoss or gaea.
Software package location for a target system - Linux format naming structure.
user - a user to be used in ecflow %EMC_USER% variable assignment.
proj - used as PROJ variable.
projenvir - user input word such as “DEV”
machine_site - user input word default as “development”
envir - user input word default as “dev”
queue - user input word default as “dev”
queue_arch - user input word default as “dev_transfer”
outputdir -  Linux format naming structure.
keepdata - user input word default as “NO”
Workflow control variable:
configure as 6 hour per cycle workflow - user input word default as “yes”
configure as one definition file - user input word default as “yes”
ptmp - storage location for COM related area.
pslot - identifier for each ecflow suite installation.
PDY - The PDY of the first cycle to be tested.
cyc - The cyc of the first cycle to be tested.



The ecflow workflow generator will have the following python modules (interface):
suite module - create ecflow suite name in the beginning of the ecflow definition file



PACKAGEHOME = ${PACKAGEROOT}/${model}/${model_ver}
